Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
map_die_package(25.10)                                  map_die_package(25.10)

Name
       map_die_package  - The command launches the MCP Editor GUI to make man-
       ual connections between package and die pins

Syntax
       map_die_package

       [-help]

       [-output <directory>]

       -package_model_file <filename>

       {-die_mcp_header  <filename>  |  -net_pad_file_pair  {{<<net1>>   <<pad
       file1>>} {<<net2>> <<pad file2>>}...}}

       The  command launches the MCP Editor GUI to make manual connections be-
       tween package and die pins. It also performs the following functions:

              * maps the voltage source files with the package model to  check
                and correct mapping information before rail analysis.

              * generates a mapping file that can be used in previous versions
                of  the  software  in case there is no mapping between die and
                package pins.

       The command has two types of inputs:

              * Voltage source files in the xy format and a package model file
                with the MCP header.

              * A circuit file with the MCP header and a  package  model  file
                with the MCP header.

       The output will be the same for both types of inputs:

              * A  ckt  mapping  file containing only the MCP header, with the
                name pkg_model_base_name + "_map"+suffix.

              * The file named  `un_mapped_bumps.txt'  will  contain  all  the
                bumps which cannot be mapped.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs the command usage and a brief description about the com-
              mand parameters.

       -die_mcp_header <filename>
              Specifies  a circuit file with the MCP header containing the die
              abstract.

       -net_pad_file_pair {{<<net1>> <<pad file1>>} {<<net2>> <<pad
       file2>>}...}
              Specifies the voltage source files mapping to each net.

       -output <directory>
              Specifies the output directory containing the mapping results.

       -package_model_file<filename>
              Specifies the name of the package model file.

Examples
              *

                The following command specifies a circuit file with MCP header
                and a package model file with the MCP header:

                map_die_package   -die_mcp_header    super_filter_mcp_ploc.ckt
                -package_model_file    C1_Voltus_4L_C1_Voltus_4L_Final_PinBas-
                eSPICE.ckt -output out_ploc

              *

                The following command specifies voltage source files in the XY
                format and a package model file with the MCP header:

                map_die_package  -output  ./out_pad  -net_pad_file_pair  {{VDD
                VDD_AO_srcs.pp}  {VDD VDD_external_srcs.pp} {VSS VSS_srcs.pp}}
                -package_model_file    C1_Voltus_4L_C1_Voltus_4L_Final_PinBas-
                eSPICE.ckt

